Add environment variables with S3 credentials to kafka in the iotivity.yml file:
  kafka-zookeeper
  environment:
    - "AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=minioTest"
    - "AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=minioTest"

Create a bucket in your S3 (here connect-test)

Create a S3 connector in the Kafka ui (confluent S3 connector) or via API with a config similar to this one with the topic you want to backup to S3 (here position-reports):
    S3 connector config
    {
      "connector.class": "io.confluent.connect.s3.S3SinkConnector",
      "s3.region": "us-east-1",
      "flush.size": "3",
      "topics": "position-reports",
      "tasks.max": "1",
      "store.url": "http://minio1:9000",
      "format.class": "io.confluent.connect.s3.format.avro.AvroFormat",
      "partitioner.class": "io.confluent.connect.storage.partitioner.DefaultPartitioner",
      "schema.generator.class": "io.confluent.connect.storage.hive.schema.DefaultSchemaGenerator",
      "name": "ConfluentConnector",
      "storage.class": "io.confluent.connect.s3.storage.S3Storage",
      "s3.bucket.name": "connect-test"
    }
    
    Now the data should be backed up.
